qkgelonsxidmdemqtgcqmkeajazkwqfcbkmifscc page 3150 Mass Rapid Transit station in Singapore NS3 Bukit Gombak 武吉甘柏 புக்கிட் கோம்பாக் Mass Rapid Transit (MRT) station Platform B of Bukit Gombak MRT station General information Location 802 Bukit Batok West Avenue 5 Singapore 659083 Coordinates 1°21′31″N 103°45′06″E﻿ / ﻿1.358702°N 103.751787°E﻿ / 1.358702; 103.751787 Operated by SMRT Trains Ltd (SMRT Corporation) Line(s) North–South Line Platforms 2 (1 island platform) Tracks 2 Connections Bus, Taxi Construction Structure type Elevated Platform levels 1 Accessible Yes History Opened 10 March 1990; 33 years ago (1990-03-10) Electrified Yes Previous names Bukit Batok North Services Preceding station Mass Rapid Transit Following station Bukit Batok towards Jurong East North–South Line Choa Chu Kang towards Marina South Pier North–South Line Future service Brickland towards Marina South Pier Location Bukit Gombak Bukit Gombak station in Singapore Bukit Gombak MRT station is an above-ground Mass Rapid Transit (MRT) station on the North South line in Bukit Batok, Singapore. Located at the junction of Bukit Batok West Avenue 5 and Bukit Batok East Avenue 5, it is the nearest MRT station to the Bukit Batok Town Park, a scenic parkland otherwise known as "Little Guilin". Opened on 10 March 1990, Bukit Gombak station was part of the Branch line before the opening of the North South line Woodlands Extension on 10 February 1996. History[edit] Installation of half-height screen doors at the station started on 30 April 2010 and operations commenced on 16 August 2010 with Clementi.[1] Then, this station was installed with high-volume low-speed fans, which commenced operations on 31 October 2012. Bukit Gombak was a temporary terminus for the North South line from 18 to 19 September 2010 during the Jurong East Modification Project upgrade.[2] and during the late openings of the MRT on Sundays from June to November 2016.[3] References[edit] ^ Wong, Siew Ying (January 26, 2008). "Above-ground MRT stations to have platform screen doors by 2012". Channel NewsAsia. Archived from the original on July 30, 2012. Retrieved February 1, 2012. ^ "LTA and SMRT gear up for disruption over the weekend". Archived from the original on 2017-08-10. Retrieved 2017-08-10. ^ "Late Opening of the East West and North South Line for maintenance works". Archived from the original on 2017-08-10. Retrieved 2017-08-10. External links[edit] Official website Wikimedia Commons has media related to Bukit Gombak MRT Station. v t e Mass Rapid Transit (MRT) stations in Singapore Italicised locations are currently not in operation North–South Line Jurong East Bukit Batok Bukit Gombak Brickland Choa Chu Kang Yew Tee Sungei Kadut Kranji Marsiling Woodlands Admiralty Sembawang Canberra Yishun Khatib Yio Chu Kang Ang Mo Kio Bishan Braddell Toa Payoh Novena Newton Orchard Somerset Dhoby Ghaut City Hall Raffles Place Marina Bay Marina South Pier Depot(s) NSL Bishan Ulu Pandan See also: Land Transport Authority SMRT Trains Trains portal Singapore portal This Singapore MRT-related article is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it. v t e contentType 24 text/html; charset=UTF-8 url 58 https://en.wikipedia.org:443/wiki/Bukit_Gombak_MRT_station responseCode 3 200 